   USGS Hurricane Mitch Program Projects

   [USEMAP:countries.jpg]
   Hurricane Mitch went directly over Honduras, Guatemala, and El
   Salvador. Nicaragua was not directly hit but was affected with flooding
   and landslides due to the extended heavy rain.
   Click on a country on the map to learn more about the devastation
   Hurricane Mitch caused, and general statistics about the country.
